5. Supplier Configuration Behavior

100 Percent Single Supplier Configuration

Example:

Supplier 4 - Lexis Nexis OTP = 100
Supplier 5 - Equifax DIT SMFA = 0
Supplier 6 - Experian CrossCore = 0

Proposed behavior:

Only supplier 4 is eligible.
Supplier 4 is selected directly.
No runtime counter update is performed.

This preserves existing behavior while avoiding database updates.

⸻

Split Supplier Configuration

Example:

Supplier 5 - Equifax DIT SMFA = 60
Supplier 4 - Lexis Nexis OTP = 40

Proposed behavior:

Total weight = 60 + 40 = 100
Random number generated between 0 and 99
0 - 59  -> Supplier 5
60 - 99 -> Supplier 4

The selected supplier is returned to the existing verification flow.

No insert or update is required during selection.

⸻

Three Supplier Configuration

Example:

Supplier 5 - Equifax DIT SMFA = 40
Supplier 4 - Lexis Nexis OTP = 35
Supplier 6 - Experian CrossCore = 25

Proposed behavior:

Total weight = 40 + 35 + 25 = 100
0 - 39  -> Supplier 5
40 - 74 -> Supplier 4
75 - 99 -> Supplier 6

The same weighted selection logic can support two or more configured suppliers.

